<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1851: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-09T17:00:00-04:00">May 9,
                                    1933—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>330. Your 630, May 6, 11 a.m. Your suggested reply to Saavedra approved,
                            particularly your emphasis on the importance of introducing the figures
                            for Latin American countries prior to signature of convention.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>